<p>This is an online 3D Minecraft map viewer and dungeon finder that requires WebGL (new Firefox/Chrome). </p>

<p>It looks like this: <br/><br/>
<center>
<iframe width="420" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/2Moe24BzPdU" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
</center>

<p><a class="clickhere" href="viewer?url=r.0.0.mca&x=172&y=67&z=189&size=3&showstuff=diamondsmoss&ymin=0">Click here to launch viewer with demo data.</a></p>

<p>(Google translate of description in case Baidu will pick it up) minecraft地图浏览器地牢发现者 (minecraft dì tú liú lǎn qì dì láo fā xiàn zhě)</p>

<h2>Step 1:&nbsp;&nbsp; Determine Minecraft coordinates and Filename</h2>
<p>To determine Minecraft coordinates, hit F3 in Minecraft. Enter x and z coordinates rounded to whole numbers below. Filename will update automatically.</p>

<p>x: &nbsp;<input id="x" name="x" size="3" type="number" value="0" />
y: &nbsp;<input id="y" name="y" size="3" type="number" value="70">
z: &nbsp;
<input id="z" name="x" size="3" type="number" value="0" /></p>

<div class="highlight"><b>YOU WILL SELECT THIS FILE FROM YOUR COMPUTER ON THE NEXT SCREEN: %appdata%/minecraft/saves/worldname/region/<span id="fname"></span></div>

<h2>Step 2: Select View Options</h2>
<input type="radio" name="show" value="all" id="showa">Show All Underground Features (very slow)
<input type="radio" name="show" value="diamondsmoss" id="showd" checked>Show Dungeons and Diamonds Only (still takes awhile)

<h2>Step 3: &nbsp;&nbsp; Launch Viewer and Select File</h2>
<p>Press the View button and on the next screen you will select the .mca file from your local machine under %appdata%/minecraft/saves/worldname/region/.</p>
<button id="view">View</button>
</div>

